 Topic: Calculator (CLI)
   
Description:
This is a simple Command Line Calculator built using Python. 
It allows the user to perform basic arithmetic operations such as addition, subtraction, multiplication, and division. 
The program continuously asks the user for inputs and operations until they choose to exit.
  
How It Works:
The calculator shows a menu of operations.
The user selects an operation (e.g., 1 for addition).
The user inputs two numbers.
The calculator performs the selected operation and displays the result.
The loop continues until the user decides to quit.
